of Kleopatra, $\\dot P_0 = 1.9\\cdot 10^{-12}$. In alternative models, with moons\ncaptured in the 3:2 mean-motion resonance or more massive moons, the respective\nvalues of $\\Delta t_2$ are a factor of 2--3 lower. Future astrometric\nobservations by direct imaging or occultations should allow to distinguish\nbetween these models, which is important for the internal structure and\nmechanical properties of (216) Kleopatra.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 25 Oct 2021 07:34:27 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-01-19"}
