n sources. This work shows that small and frequent\nfeatures, which were previously neglected, can cause strong upflows in the\nsolar corona. These results emphasise the importance of the first observations\nfrom the Extreme-Ultraviolet Imager (EUI) onboard Solar Orbiter, which revealed\ncomplex small-scale coronal structures.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 25 Oct 2021 09:25:29 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-12-15"}
